<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=103&amp;p=613#p613"><![CDATA[
The FF1&amp;2 cartridge definitely has two 8k SRAMs, one for each game.  On emulators (which treat the game as having a single 8k SRAM) playing FF2 erases the FF1 saved game, and playing FF1 even as far as the Continue/New Game screen erases the first FF2 save slot (it erases all of them if you actually start playing the game)<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Fri Dec 17, 2004 9:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
